;; ============================================================================
;; USAGE NOTES
;; ============================================================================
;;
;; To activate this experimental config:
;;   just kanata-test-experimental
;;
;; BASE LAYER - Verify mappings work:
;;   1. Press physical 3 4 5 6 7 → should output: q w e r t
;;   2. Press physical W E R T Y → should output: a s d f g
;;   3. Press physical A S D F G → should output: z x c v b
;;   4. Press physical 8 9 0 - = → should output: y u i o p
;;   5. Press physical I O P [ ] → should output: h j k l ;
;;   6. Press physical K L ; ' \ → should output: n m , . enter
;;
;; ESSENTIAL KEYS:
;;   - Space: Physical spacebar
;;   - Enter: Physical \ (backslash key, shifted-up caps row)
;;   - Tab: Tap physical c (on traditional bottom row)
;;   - Escape: Tap physical x (on traditional bottom row)
;;   - Comma: Physical ; key (outputs ,)
;;   - Period: Physical ' key (outputs .)
;;
;; MODIFIERS (on traditional bottom row - X C V):
;;   - Ctrl: Hold physical x (tap=Escape, hold=Ctrl)
;;   - Option/Alt: Hold physical c (tap=Tab, hold=Option)
;;   - Cmd: Hold physical v (hold only)
;;
;;   Vim usage examples:
;;     - Ctrl+D: Hold x + press R (outputs D) = Ctrl+D (scroll down)
;;     - Ctrl+U: Hold x + press U = Ctrl+U (scroll up)
;;     - Ctrl+W: Hold x + press 4 (outputs W) = Ctrl+W (window commands)
;;     - Ctrl+C: Hold x + press D (outputs C) = Ctrl+C (interrupt)
;;
;;   Mac shortcuts:
;;     - Cmd+C: Hold v + press D (outputs C) = Cmd+C (copy)
;;     - Cmd+V: Hold v + press F (outputs V) = Cmd+V (paste)
;;     - Cmd+Tab: Hold v + tap c = Cmd+Tab (app switch)
;;
;; LAYER ACTIVATORS (hold these keys):
;;   - Physical m (traditional bottom row) → Shift layer (uppercase letters)
;;   - Physical . (period on traditional bottom row) → Nav layer (numbers, arrows)
;;   - Physical , (comma on traditional bottom row) → Symbol layer (symbols)
;;
;; SYMBOL LAYER - Hold physical comma key
;;   Top row:
;;     Hold comma + press 3 4 5 6 7 → should output: ! @ # $ %
;;     Hold comma + press 8 9 0 - = → should output: ^ & * ` ~
;;   Home row:
;;     Hold comma + press W E R T → should output: " [ { (
;;     Hold comma + press I O P [ ] → should output: / - = : ;
;;   Bottom row:
;;     Hold comma + press A S D F → should output: ' ] } )
;;     Hold comma + press K L ; ' \ → should output: \ _ + | ?
;;
;; SHIFT LAYER - Hold physical m key
;;   Hold m + press any alpha key → outputs uppercase letter
;;   Hold m + press physical ; ' \ → should output: < > ?
;;
;; NAV LAYER - Hold physical . (period) key
;;   Numbers:
;;     Hold . + press 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 0 - = → should output: 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 0
;;   Arrow keys (Vim style):
;;     Hold . + press I O P [ → should output: Left Down Up Right
;;   Navigation:
;;     Hold . + press K L ; ' → should output: Home PgDn PgUp End
;;   Clipboard:
;;     Hold . + press A S D F → should output: Undo Cut Copy Paste (Ctrl+Z/X/C/V)
;;   Backspace:
;;     Hold . + press ] → should output: Backspace
;;
;; MODIFIER + LAYER COMBINATIONS:
;;   You can combine modifiers with Nav layer. Examples:
;;     - Ctrl+arrows: Hold x (Ctrl) + Hold . (Nav) + press I/O/P/[ → Ctrl+arrows
;;     - Cmd+arrows: Hold v (Cmd) + Hold . (Nav) + press I/O/P/[ → Cmd+arrows
;;     - Option+arrows: Hold c (Option) + Hold . (Nav) + press I/O/P/[ → Option+arrows
;;     - Perfect for Vim text navigation and selection!
;;
;; LAYOUT SUMMARY - Traditional Bottom Row:
;;   Physical:  z     x           c           v         m         ,         .
;;   Function:  _     ESC/CTRL    TAB/OPT     CMD       SHIFT     SYMBOL    NAV
;;                    tap/hold    tap/hold    (hold)    (hold)    (hold)    (hold)
;;
;; vim: set ft=lisp
